               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>moveUp</name>
                  <description>Moves the child block with the given index up the list by one where the very top of the list is index 0. If the given index is already at the top of the list or out of range then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given index is at the top of the list or is out of range then return, else swap the child with the given index with the child just above it and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child moved interface and continue calling the next parent's child moved interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child block moved up by one.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>moveDown</name>
                  <description>Moves the child block with the given index down the list by one where the very top of the list is index 0. If the given index is already at the bottom of the list or out of range then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given index is at the top of the list or is out of range then return, else swap the child with the given index with the child just below it and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child moved interface and continue calling the next parent's child moved interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child block moved down by one.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>insert</name>
                  <description>Inserts a new child block into this block's list of children at the given index. If the given index is less than 0 it is prepended to this block's list, else if the given index is greater than this block's list size then it is appended. If the given pointer to the new block is null or it is a type this block cannot contain then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given child pointer is null or its type is not contained in this blocks build list then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Insert the new block into this block's list of children at the given index, releasing it from its smart pointer and setting this block as its parent. Call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child added interface and continue calling the next parent's child added interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index where the new block is inserted.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the new block that is inserted as this block's child.</description>
                     <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock>&amp;&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>take</name>
                  <description>Takes the child block at the given index this block contains. The child block returned no longer has a parent. If the index is out of range then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <return_description>Pointer to child that was taken from this block.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is out of range then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Remove the child at the given index from this block's list of children saving its pointer to the smart pointer _ret_. Call the child removed interface and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child removed interface with _ret_ and continue calling the next parent's child removed interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child that is taken.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>remove</name>
                  <description>Removes the child block at the given index, deleting it and any children it may contain. If the given index is out of range then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child that is removed and deleted.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>read</name>
                  <description>Reads in block data from an XML element. This clears any existing data this block contains, including the removal and deletion of all existing children. This recursively adds any children contained in the XML reading in their data from child XML elements.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Delete and clear any existing children this block may contain.</operation>
                  <operation>Iterate through all children nodes of the given element. If a child is an element and matches the data tag then read it in as this block's new data, else if it an element that read it in as a new child block.</operation>
                  <operation>Make sure all new children of this block is allowed to this block's child using its built list interface. If any child is found that is not allowed then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>The XML element that stores block data this block reads as input.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="0">
                  <name>write</name>
                  <description>Writes out this block's data as an XML element. This includes all children as child XML elements which have their write functions called recursively.</description>
                  <const/>
                  <type>QDomElement</type>
                  <return_description>XML element that stores this block's data and all children underneath it.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new XML element _data_ writing all of this block's data to it.</operation>
                  <operation>Create a new XML element _ret_. Adding this block's type to _ret_ as an attribute and appending the _data_ element. Iterate through this block's list of children, calling their write method and appending the returned child element to _ret_.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="0">
                     <name>document</name>
                     <type>QDomDocument&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
